parameters: \nc<>...Something feels different from what I was expecting.

\nc<>(From my perspective, it was somewhat as expected. But for
Sachiko, it's still...)

\nc<>Yeah. I was actually planning to wait a little longer and
see how things go, but... I can't wait any longer than this.
\nc<>Y-Yes? What is it, Kei-san? Your face looks scary.
\nc<>I have something I want to talk about.

\nc<>It might be a difficult story for Sachiko-chan, but I still
want you to listen.

\nc<>So, to summarize, Kei-san is a magical girl who came chasing
after the villain, right?

\nc<>The cult leader is a villain who manipulates their followers
with hypnosis.
\nc<>That's right, me being Kei's partner is the proof.

\nc<>Suddenly acquiring a large building, not being able to meet
the cult leader easily, and the saints and apostles turning
into zombies.

\nc<>But I can't accept it. After all, it's that cult leader, you
know?

\nc<>I, or rather, I haven't been able to trust people much
since before.

\nc<>So I didn't have any friends, couldn't go to school
properly, and I wandered around the town all the time.

\nc<>Originally, defective products like this should be disposed
of as a matter of course...

\nc<>It was my first time. The cult leader was the first one to
tell me that it's okay for me to stay here even if I don't
change.

\nc<>Such a person manipulating others as they please, like a
villain, is unthinkable...

\nc<>This won't do nya. I showed them my true form, but if
this is the extent...

\nc<>There is a high probability that she has been subjected to
something. We should use magic and escape immediately.
\nc<>...I don't know if these words will be comforting, but...

\nc<>This is the first time I've seen a case where a person
becomes a villain. There might be some kind of cause behind
it.

\nc<>Before the attack incident this time, the cult leader didn't
hypnotize the ordinary believers either.

\nc<>If there is a possibility to return him to normal, it would
be you or the aunties.

\nc<>Please, let's together return the cult leader to their
original form.

\nc<>If it's not that the cult leader has changed, but rather if
the cult leader was originally a bad villain...
\nc<>Will you let the cult leader escape again this time?

\nc<>That was a mean question. I'm sorry. I won't tell anyone
that I'm a magical girl.

\nc<>But, it doesn't seem like I can be of any help to you, Kei-
san.
